WEBVTT

00:03.742 --> 00:04.134
.

00:04.178 --> 00:06.658
- Previously on
"Midnight, Texas."

00:06.702 --> 00:07.746
- Bad things keep
happening to Bobo

00:07.790 --> 00:09.313
because our family is cursed.

00:09.357 --> 00:11.315
The kind of dark magic
that I warned you about.

00:11.359 --> 00:14.536
- As long as Bobo loves me,
he's gonna die.

00:14.579 --> 00:16.320
It's over.

00:16.364 --> 00:18.496
- My dad, he wasn't there
when I was a kid.

00:18.540 --> 00:22.674
The last person I let myself
rely on was my stepmother.

00:22.718 --> 00:25.329
- You're not turning.
- I went to see Kai.

00:25.373 --> 00:26.765
He cured me.
I have to go.

00:26.809 --> 00:28.158
It's time for me
to leave Midnight.

00:28.202 --> 00:29.551
- How you holding up?

00:29.594 --> 00:31.074
- Creek and I have
been through worse.

00:31.118 --> 00:33.120
- I didn't know that you
just had a break up.

00:33.163 --> 00:35.905
- Oh, it's more of a...
a break than a break up.

00:35.948 --> 00:37.689
- Well, I just thought
because she moved away...

00:37.733 --> 00:39.865
- I think you and I should
get those drinks.

00:39.909 --> 00:41.476
- It's a date.

00:45.349 --> 00:48.700
[Jade Bird's "Uh Huh"]

00:48.744 --> 00:50.354
- [whimpering]
- ♪ She got you

00:50.398 --> 00:53.183
♪ On your knees
like a little boy ♪

00:53.227 --> 00:57.187
♪ Everybody sees that
you're just a little toy ♪

00:57.231 --> 01:00.886
♪ She's got a boxful that
her daddy likely bought ♪

01:00.930 --> 01:04.716
♪ She asks you if you love her
and you nod and say... ♪

01:04.760 --> 01:07.676
- [groaning]

01:07.719 --> 01:11.158
[panting, crying]

01:11.201 --> 01:14.161
[intense music]

01:14.204 --> 01:19.688
♪

01:19.731 --> 01:23.257
[screaming, gasping]

01:23.300 --> 01:29.176
♪

01:29.219 --> 01:31.439
[panting]

01:33.223 --> 01:37.140
[screaming]

01:37.184 --> 01:41.536
[whimpering, groaning]

01:41.579 --> 01:44.147
[tearing]

01:49.152 --> 01:52.329
- [sniffing]

01:54.331 --> 01:59.119
[baby crying]

01:59.162 --> 02:06.387
♪

02:14.221 --> 02:18.181
- "Rev, her name is Mary.
Please help her."

02:18.225 --> 02:22.446
- [crying]
- Okay, Mary. Okay.

02:25.580 --> 02:27.625
- [crying]

02:27.669 --> 02:29.801
♪

02:29.845 --> 02:31.803
[Phosphorescent's
"New Birth In New England"]

02:31.847 --> 02:33.457
[both laughing]

02:33.501 --> 02:35.633
- Wait, wait, wait.
Hold on.

02:35.677 --> 02:39.376
You were driving around
the country in that old RV

02:39.420 --> 02:42.031
with your dead grandma inside?
- Doesn't everyone?

02:42.074 --> 02:43.250
- No.

02:43.293 --> 02:44.642
[both laughing]

02:44.686 --> 02:46.383
- I'm glad we're finally
having those drinks.

02:46.427 --> 02:48.951
- Ah, I can't thank you enough
for cleansing the hotel.

02:48.994 --> 02:50.170
Hmm.

02:50.213 --> 02:52.650
- You gotta lick it first.
The salt.

02:52.694 --> 02:55.436
- ♪ I was thinking
about another beer ♪

02:55.479 --> 02:57.655
- Mmm.
- Ah.

02:57.699 --> 03:01.093
- ♪ It had a lady playing
on the piano ♪

03:01.137 --> 03:03.661
- You all right?

03:03.705 --> 03:07.448
- Oh, I was just thinking
how much I needed this.

03:07.491 --> 03:11.408
- The tequila?
- A night out.

03:11.452 --> 03:14.194
With someone who
is actually interested

03:14.237 --> 03:16.021
in what I had to say.

03:16.065 --> 03:18.023
- ♪ I said well I'm sitting
in a bar in New England ♪

03:18.067 --> 03:20.374
- Wanna talk about it?
- Look, don't get me wrong.

03:20.417 --> 03:23.507
Kai's a good man.

03:23.551 --> 03:26.380
But he's just got
a demanding career.

03:26.423 --> 03:28.773
And he's away a lot.

03:28.817 --> 03:32.647
With a bunch of young,
impressionable women.

03:32.690 --> 03:35.780
- Lyric and Sequoia.
- Yeah, to name a few.

03:35.824 --> 03:38.043
It just makes me wonder
what they're doing

03:38.087 --> 03:41.221
when they're away working.
- Yeah, that's gotta be hard.

03:41.264 --> 03:42.831
- [sighs]

03:42.874 --> 03:45.399
Well, no relationship
is perfect, huh?

03:45.442 --> 03:47.879
- I'll drink to that.
- Yeah, me, too.

03:47.923 --> 03:49.403
[chuckles]

03:51.143 --> 03:53.145
Whoo!

03:53.189 --> 03:55.278
You wanna talk about Creek?

03:55.322 --> 03:59.151
- Um, there's nothing
to talk about, really.

03:59.195 --> 04:02.329
Midnight wasn't for her.
- Hmm.

04:02.372 --> 04:04.374
But is it for you?

04:04.418 --> 04:07.247
- When people like me
find a place like this,

04:07.290 --> 04:08.422
we tend to stay.

04:08.465 --> 04:10.293
- Well, we're lucky
to have you.

04:10.337 --> 04:12.948
- Yeah, well...

04:12.991 --> 04:15.124
[both chuckle]

04:15.167 --> 04:18.170
[cell phone rings]

04:18.214 --> 04:20.738
Um, hey.
What's going on?

04:20.782 --> 04:24.220
- You need to get
to the church now.

04:24.264 --> 04:25.700
[dramatic music]

04:25.743 --> 04:28.659
- Where's Chuy?
- Paris.

04:28.703 --> 04:31.096
Uh, Texas.
At "Nail-A-Palooza."

04:31.140 --> 04:32.663
- Hey, Fij, we need to talk.

04:32.707 --> 04:33.969
- Oh, really,
it's not a good time.

04:34.012 --> 04:36.493
- Oh.
Oh, my God.

04:37.364 --> 04:38.974
What happened?

04:40.105 --> 04:41.455
Well, I--I'm sorry to crash.

04:41.498 --> 04:44.109
I just thought maybe
I could help.

04:44.153 --> 04:45.459
- Did something attack her?

04:45.502 --> 04:47.635
- I believe it happened
in childbirth.

04:47.678 --> 04:50.115
- Well, maybe her ghost
can tell us something.

04:50.159 --> 04:54.206
♪

04:54.250 --> 04:56.296
- Nothing.

04:56.339 --> 04:58.385
- There's ligature marks
on her wrist.

04:58.428 --> 05:00.822
- From what?
- Looks like shackles.

05:00.865 --> 05:03.607
- What about that burn
mark on her arm?

05:03.651 --> 05:06.306
- Scars.
My guess is a stun gun.

05:06.349 --> 05:08.438
- So she was being
held captive?

05:08.482 --> 05:10.135
- Why come here?

05:10.179 --> 05:11.963
- She was looking for the Rev.

05:12.007 --> 05:13.487
- Any idea how he knew her?

05:13.530 --> 05:16.228
- No, but I can tell you
the child's name.

05:16.272 --> 05:18.492
Mary.

05:18.535 --> 05:20.972
[snarling, baby crying]

05:21.016 --> 05:24.062
[crunching]

05:24.106 --> 05:26.238
[knife clinks]

05:26.282 --> 05:28.980
- What--I'm confused.

05:29.024 --> 05:30.808
- What the hell is she?

05:34.029 --> 05:36.379
[child cooing]

05:39.426 --> 05:40.992
- [stutters]

05:42.080 --> 05:46.084
- Hey, sweetie.
Can we have a little talk?

05:46.128 --> 05:47.521
Yeah?

05:49.871 --> 05:53.831
She wants to feed.
- On what?

05:53.875 --> 05:55.355
- Meat.

05:56.878 --> 05:59.446
I think we know why that woman
was looking for the Rev.

05:59.489 --> 06:02.362
Violent child birth,
carnivore...

06:02.405 --> 06:05.713
- Growling,
accelerated growth...

06:05.756 --> 06:07.976
[both]
She's a were-tiger.

06:08.019 --> 06:13.764
♪

06:13.808 --> 06:16.027
- You really think it's safe
bringing a were-tiger

06:16.071 --> 06:18.856
into our home?
- She's just a toddler.

06:18.900 --> 06:22.033
She's harmless, at least
until the next full moon.

06:22.077 --> 06:23.774
And that's weeks away.

06:23.818 --> 06:26.298
- It doesn't freak you out
that she grew three years

06:26.342 --> 06:29.998
in three minutes?
- It stops at 18.

06:30.041 --> 06:33.175
- Oh.
[chuckles]

06:33.218 --> 06:36.221
What is she doing here?

06:36.265 --> 06:37.919
- It takes a village.

06:37.962 --> 06:40.095
- Where's the rest
of the villagers?

06:40.138 --> 06:43.141
- They are trying to track down
where the mother came from.

06:43.185 --> 06:45.143
Joe is trying to track
down the Rev.

06:45.187 --> 06:47.450
Manfred and Patience
are searching the truck.

06:47.494 --> 06:49.713
Least I could do was take
the night shift.

06:49.757 --> 06:51.628
- Yeah, but that's
another thing.

06:51.672 --> 06:54.414
Why did Manfred bring
Patience with him?

06:54.457 --> 06:55.719
- Why does that bother you?

06:55.763 --> 06:58.548
- Uh, for one,
her name's Patience.

06:58.592 --> 07:00.985
I don't trust her.
- Fiji did a spell.

07:01.029 --> 07:02.726
Her intentions are good.

07:02.770 --> 07:06.948
- Uh, when did you
become so paternal?

07:06.991 --> 07:10.473
- We never talked about it
before because we never had to.

07:10.517 --> 07:13.389
But in my previous life,
I wanted kids.

07:14.346 --> 07:18.002
You ever think about it?
- Lem, my dad abandoned me.

07:18.046 --> 07:22.442
And my stepmom pimped me out
to support her pill addiction.

07:22.485 --> 07:26.663
So, no, I haven't really felt
warm and fuzzy about family.

07:26.707 --> 07:31.494
- I understand,
but having a child

07:31.538 --> 07:33.888
has a way of healing the past.

07:33.931 --> 07:36.760
- [chuckles]

07:36.804 --> 07:38.109
Yeah.

07:39.720 --> 07:42.853
That is a hard no.

07:42.897 --> 07:46.030
[country rock music]

07:46.074 --> 07:48.642
♪

07:55.475 --> 07:57.128
- [sniffing]

07:57.172 --> 07:59.914
- So you dumped the big lug
but you didn't tell him

07:59.957 --> 08:01.524
the real reason.

08:01.568 --> 08:03.744
- [sniffles]

08:03.787 --> 08:06.486
If I told him
that it was a family curse,

08:06.529 --> 08:12.056
he wouldn't stop loving me,
which means with or without me,

08:12.100 --> 08:14.537
he--he'd be...

08:14.581 --> 08:16.321
- A dead man walking.

08:16.365 --> 08:19.150
- Exactly.

08:19.194 --> 08:24.765
So this way he'll suffer
some heartbreak now.

08:26.636 --> 08:28.638
But he'll still be alive.

08:28.682 --> 08:30.335
Eventually move on.

08:30.379 --> 08:32.860
[Edwin McCain's "I'll Be"
plays in the distance]

08:32.903 --> 08:34.644
- ♪ Dress it up

08:34.688 --> 08:37.517
♪ With the trappings of love

08:37.560 --> 08:40.041
♪ I'll be captivated

08:40.084 --> 08:42.347
♪ I'll hang
from your lips instead... ♪

08:42.391 --> 08:44.262
- [laughs]

08:44.306 --> 08:48.136
♪ Of the gallows of heartache
that hang from above ♪

08:48.179 --> 08:50.747
- So much for moving on.

08:53.358 --> 08:59.364
- ♪ I'll be
your cryin' shoulder ♪

08:59.408 --> 09:01.628
♪ I'll be--

09:01.671 --> 09:03.891
- Go home, Bobo.

09:04.892 --> 09:07.938
- Not until I get some answers.

09:07.982 --> 09:09.549
One minute we're
moving in together,

09:09.592 --> 09:11.420
next minute you're
breaking up with me?

09:11.463 --> 09:13.204
It doesn't make any sense.

09:13.248 --> 09:17.252
- I told you Aunt Mildred said
we're not meant to be together.

09:17.295 --> 09:20.255
- [stutters] That--that
is ridiculous.

09:20.298 --> 09:23.258
Hey, if this has something
to do with my--

09:23.301 --> 09:25.913
my string of bad luck...

09:25.956 --> 09:28.002
we could figure
it out together.

09:30.134 --> 09:31.658
We're soul mates.

09:32.659 --> 09:34.922
Please don't give up on me,
Fij.

09:37.751 --> 09:40.014
- I'm sorry, Bobo.
It's over.

09:45.019 --> 09:47.891
- Well, I'm never
giving up on you.

09:47.935 --> 09:51.982
- ♪ I'll be better
when I'm older ♪

09:52.026 --> 09:54.855
- Looks like you're gonna
need a new plan.

09:54.898 --> 09:57.031
[dramatic music]

09:57.074 --> 09:59.555
- [grunts]

09:59.599 --> 10:01.078
Any chance you have a crowbar?

10:01.122 --> 10:02.123
- Uh, yeah.

10:02.166 --> 10:04.429
We've got one
in the storage room.

10:04.473 --> 10:08.346
♪

10:08.390 --> 10:10.958
Uh, there's nothing
inside her glove box.

10:12.699 --> 10:15.310
- Because this isn't her truck.

10:15.353 --> 10:16.790
The ignition's hotwired.

10:16.833 --> 10:18.705
I think she stole it to escape.

10:19.967 --> 10:23.231
- Well, a trapped woman
will do desperate things.

10:25.494 --> 10:26.756
- [grunts]

10:26.800 --> 10:33.676
♪

10:33.720 --> 10:36.200
Think this is Mary's dad?

10:36.244 --> 10:40.074
- Well, if it is,
maybe he's still out there.

10:41.728 --> 10:44.600
What was this poor
woman running from?

10:44.644 --> 10:51.433
♪

10:54.479 --> 10:56.873
[electricity sparking]

10:56.917 --> 10:59.354
- Let's go find the bitch.

11:00.529 --> 11:01.922
Come on.

11:08.015 --> 11:08.406
.

11:08.450 --> 11:09.625
[tablet playing videos]

11:09.669 --> 11:11.409
- [groans]

11:11.453 --> 11:14.195
Here.
Yeah?

11:14.238 --> 11:17.154
Oh, yeah.
That's...

11:17.198 --> 11:20.767
Really--Okay.
Whoo!

11:20.810 --> 11:24.205
Look.
Yeah.

11:24.248 --> 11:28.296
Your new best friend.
Okay.

11:28.339 --> 11:29.863
[sighs]

11:29.906 --> 11:31.734
[stomping]

11:31.778 --> 11:33.257
Oh, Lem.

11:33.301 --> 11:34.868
- I'm trying to get some sleep.

11:34.911 --> 11:36.130
- Oh.

11:36.173 --> 11:37.827
Well, I'm trying
to keep my sanity.

11:37.871 --> 11:40.700
- Just try and do your best
until sundown.

11:40.743 --> 11:42.223
- [chuckles]

11:42.266 --> 11:44.007
I won't make it till sundown.

11:44.051 --> 11:45.356
You don't understand.

11:45.400 --> 11:47.619
This place is a pigsty
and, I mean,

11:47.663 --> 11:50.231
she's all over the place.
And then there's the questions.

11:50.274 --> 11:52.494
She treats me like I'm Siri.

11:52.537 --> 11:54.191
- Olivia, She barely knows how
to talk.

11:54.235 --> 11:56.846
- [laughs]

11:56.890 --> 11:58.021
Not so much.

11:58.065 --> 11:59.806
See, she's been watching
cartoons all day,

11:59.849 --> 12:04.158
and apparently she absorbs
language as fast as she grows.

12:04.201 --> 12:05.812
Yeah.
[laughs]

12:05.855 --> 12:07.901
- [gasps]

12:07.944 --> 12:09.424
- Lem?

12:09.467 --> 12:13.080
- [coughing]
- Lem?

12:13.123 --> 12:14.472
[stomping]

12:14.516 --> 12:18.128
Lem!
- We're out of meat.

12:18.172 --> 12:21.262
[dramatic music]

12:21.305 --> 12:23.394
- Holy...

12:23.438 --> 12:25.483
- Can I change?

12:25.527 --> 12:27.268
It's too small.

12:27.311 --> 12:29.661
And I hate purple.

12:29.705 --> 12:31.663
- Here.
- I don't like that.

12:31.707 --> 12:35.189
- Well, you can put this on
or you can stay in that shirt.

12:35.232 --> 12:36.712
Your choice.

12:40.368 --> 12:41.499
Good choice.

12:41.543 --> 12:44.067
- Why am I growing so fast?

12:44.111 --> 12:48.289
- Uh, it's complicated.

12:48.332 --> 12:49.986
- Why?

12:50.030 --> 12:53.294
- Because.
- Because isn't an answer.

12:53.337 --> 12:55.122
- Oh, my God.

12:55.165 --> 12:59.126
- Olivia, where's my real mom?

12:59.169 --> 13:02.956
- Look, kid, I'm not gonna
sugar coat this for you.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.827
Your mom's gone.

13:04.871 --> 13:08.526
[dramatic music]

13:08.570 --> 13:11.486
Which means that you
have to grow up.

13:11.529 --> 13:14.750
Fast.
- Did you have to grow up fast?

13:14.794 --> 13:16.056
- Yeah, but for
different reasons.

13:16.099 --> 13:19.407
- What reasons?
- It doesn't matter.

13:21.322 --> 13:24.194
I know what it's like
to lose your mom.

13:24.238 --> 13:26.501
Mine died when I was nine.

13:26.544 --> 13:28.372
- Where was your dad?

13:30.592 --> 13:32.420
- That's a good question.

13:35.989 --> 13:37.904
Look, The point is,

13:37.947 --> 13:41.864
the only person
you can depend on is yourself.

13:43.910 --> 13:45.607
- Are you mad at me?

13:48.044 --> 13:49.480
- No.

13:52.222 --> 13:53.833
It's not you I'm mad at.

13:53.876 --> 13:56.618
[sizzling]

13:56.661 --> 14:03.277
♪

14:03.320 --> 14:04.539
[door opens]

14:04.582 --> 14:09.544
♪

14:09.587 --> 14:11.459
- Hey.
- Brought you a coffee.

14:11.502 --> 14:13.548
- [chuckles]

14:14.418 --> 14:16.159
Thank you.
Um...

14:16.203 --> 14:17.987
[chair dragging across floor]

14:18.031 --> 14:20.555
♪

14:20.598 --> 14:22.557
- I know I've been cold.

14:22.600 --> 14:24.080
- I don't understand.

14:24.124 --> 14:27.910
- Yeah, I know,
that--that's why I'm here.

14:27.954 --> 14:30.043
You know, I've been
thinking about us a lot.

14:30.086 --> 14:33.481
We share so much.

14:33.524 --> 14:36.876
Midnight.
Friends.

14:36.919 --> 14:40.488
I just want this to work
for both of us.

14:40.531 --> 14:41.663
- So do I.

14:41.706 --> 14:43.273
- That's why we
need to figure out

14:43.317 --> 14:45.667
a way
to consciously uncouple.

14:47.625 --> 14:49.149
- Well, I have no idea
what that means,

14:49.192 --> 14:52.848
but like I said before,
I'm not giving up on us.

14:55.459 --> 14:57.897
Mmm.
Yeah, that coffee tastes funny.

14:57.940 --> 15:00.377
- It's artisanal.
[chuckles]

15:00.421 --> 15:02.249
Drink up.

15:02.292 --> 15:08.864
♪

15:08.908 --> 15:12.085
- All relationships
face obstacles.

15:12.128 --> 15:13.303
- Mm-hmm.

15:13.347 --> 15:14.609
- And if we want
this badly enough,

15:14.652 --> 15:16.002
then we can find a way
to make it work.

15:16.045 --> 15:18.482
That's what people
who love each other--

15:18.526 --> 15:21.877
that's what they do.
They...

15:24.880 --> 15:27.883
They, um...
- Bobo.

15:33.323 --> 15:35.847
You need to--to let me go.

15:35.891 --> 15:37.719
You have to forget about me.

15:37.762 --> 15:41.462
- N--No, I--I could--I could
never forget about you.

15:41.505 --> 15:43.116
- You have to.

15:43.159 --> 15:46.641
And the tincture I put in your
coffee is gonna make you do it.

15:46.684 --> 15:50.166
- What--Wait, what?
Wh--What are you t--

15:51.907 --> 15:54.040
Um...
[chuckles]

15:54.083 --> 15:56.651
I, uh...

15:56.694 --> 16:00.394
What was I saying?
- I'm sorry, Bobo.

16:00.437 --> 16:03.005
It was the only way
to save your life.

16:03.049 --> 16:06.617
- Um, no, I'm sorry.

16:06.661 --> 16:10.491
I completely lost
my train of thought.

16:10.534 --> 16:12.493
Who are you, again?

16:12.536 --> 16:14.364
- [inhales deeply]

16:14.408 --> 16:17.715
I am Fiji Cavanaugh.

16:17.759 --> 16:19.195
It's nice to meet you.

16:19.239 --> 16:21.632
- Well, it's good to meet you,
Fiji Cavanaugh.

16:23.591 --> 16:27.029
[clang]

16:27.073 --> 16:29.423
- Looks like you've
done this before.

16:29.466 --> 16:32.165
- Skills of a misspent youth.

16:32.208 --> 16:35.559
[rattling]

16:35.603 --> 16:38.214
- What in the world are those?

16:38.258 --> 16:40.477
- Shock collars.

16:40.521 --> 16:42.218
And I don't think
they're for pets.

16:42.262 --> 16:44.003
- Not my kind of party.

16:44.046 --> 16:46.440
- Django, I thought
that bitch'd be in there.

16:46.483 --> 16:48.746
- I don't care what you think.

16:48.790 --> 16:56.015
♪

16:58.887 --> 17:01.759
Look what some asswipe
did to your lock.

17:01.803 --> 17:03.500
- Damn.

17:03.544 --> 17:08.592
♪

17:08.636 --> 17:10.551
- I'll bet the bitch
had the baby.

17:10.594 --> 17:12.248
- Then let's find the damn kid.

17:12.292 --> 17:13.815
- Yep.

17:17.340 --> 17:18.472
[both breathing heavy]

17:18.515 --> 17:20.561
- We gotta warn Olivia.

17:20.604 --> 17:22.867
- Mary?

17:25.435 --> 17:26.958
Mary?

17:31.267 --> 17:32.747
[dramatic music]

17:32.790 --> 17:35.619
[cell phone rings]

17:35.663 --> 17:36.620
Yeah?

17:36.664 --> 17:37.882
- We got trouble.

17:37.926 --> 17:39.623
A couple of thugs
looking for Mary.

17:39.667 --> 17:44.802
♪

17:44.846 --> 17:47.022
[door rattling]

17:49.720 --> 17:51.635
[gun cocking]

17:53.333 --> 17:54.595
[squeaking]

17:54.638 --> 17:56.640
- Playtime's over.

17:58.642 --> 17:59.774
- Who's--No!

17:59.817 --> 18:00.818
Stop!
No!

18:00.862 --> 18:02.603
Get away from me!

18:02.646 --> 18:04.257
[screaming, blows landing]

18:04.300 --> 18:05.432
- Mary.

18:05.475 --> 18:06.781
Mary!

18:06.824 --> 18:10.567
♪

18:10.611 --> 18:13.048
- [snarling]

18:13.092 --> 18:14.354
- Mary?

18:14.397 --> 18:20.273
♪

18:20.316 --> 18:21.665
It's okay.

18:25.539 --> 18:25.713
.

18:25.756 --> 18:27.149
- It's okay.

18:27.193 --> 18:29.804
It's me.

18:29.847 --> 18:32.111
Olivia.

18:32.154 --> 18:34.025
[suspenseful music]

18:34.069 --> 18:37.246
- I don't know what
happened to me.

18:37.290 --> 18:40.815
[crying]
I'm so sorry.

18:40.858 --> 18:42.773
[crying]

18:42.817 --> 18:45.776
[dramatic music]

18:45.820 --> 18:49.171
♪

18:49.215 --> 18:52.957
- Olivia, um...

18:53.001 --> 18:54.785
Here.

18:54.829 --> 18:56.570
- Here you go.

18:56.613 --> 18:58.789
All right, come with me, okay?

19:00.269 --> 19:02.228
- Any luck contacting the Rev?

19:02.271 --> 19:04.360
- No. I followed every
lead I could find.

19:04.404 --> 19:05.709
Nada.
- I don't understand.

19:05.753 --> 19:07.189
What happened?
- Me, neither.

19:07.233 --> 19:08.712
It doesn't make any sense.

19:08.756 --> 19:11.367
If--If Mary's a were-tiger,
how can she turn when it's not

19:11.411 --> 19:12.368
a full moon?

19:12.412 --> 19:14.283
- Blame it on puberty.

19:14.327 --> 19:15.719
I did a little research.

19:15.763 --> 19:17.199
Apparently when a were
is in development,

19:17.243 --> 19:19.245
their cycles are
all out of whack.

19:19.288 --> 19:21.812
Just like in humans.
It's hormonal.

19:21.856 --> 19:23.466
- And I thought junior
high was tough.

19:23.510 --> 19:26.339
- It must have been scary
for her to turn like that.

19:26.382 --> 19:28.384
[approaching sirens]

19:28.428 --> 19:29.733
- Damn.

19:29.777 --> 19:32.083
Looks like we've got some
'splaining to do.

19:32.127 --> 19:33.520
[emergency sirens blaring]

19:33.563 --> 19:36.914
- Hotel guests heard screams.
Called 911.

19:36.958 --> 19:40.396
- What happened to those two
men is just awful.

19:40.440 --> 19:41.745
[all sigh]

19:41.789 --> 19:44.183
- Hm.
- Nobody saw anything?

19:44.226 --> 19:48.404
- Just looks like an animal
attack to me, officer.

19:48.448 --> 19:49.927
- Always does.

19:49.971 --> 19:52.321
Must be some real vicious
animals here in Midnight.

19:52.365 --> 19:54.018
- Must be.

19:56.456 --> 19:58.240
- Load 'em up.

19:58.284 --> 20:00.938
I wanna get outta here.
Pronto.

20:04.464 --> 20:06.335
- What are you looking at,
dinlo?

20:08.468 --> 20:10.687
- Romanichal?

20:10.731 --> 20:13.777
- Yeah, I'm a gypsy.
What's it to you?

20:13.821 --> 20:17.955
♪

20:17.999 --> 20:19.218
- Manfred.

20:19.261 --> 20:21.350
Were you talking to someone?

20:21.394 --> 20:24.135
- One of their ghosts.

20:24.179 --> 20:25.963
But he just got away.

20:28.270 --> 20:30.316
We gotta get to the morgue.

20:32.318 --> 20:35.538
- What's wrong with me?
- Nothing.

20:35.582 --> 20:37.192
- Am I some kind of freak
or something?

20:37.236 --> 20:40.282
- No.
You're special.

20:40.326 --> 20:43.285
And you're smart.

20:43.329 --> 20:45.679
And you're very strong.
[chuckles]

20:45.722 --> 20:47.724
- But special means different.

20:47.768 --> 20:49.813
And I don't wanna be different.

20:49.857 --> 20:53.164
- But being different
is really cool.

20:53.208 --> 20:56.037
- Yeah.
He should know.

20:56.080 --> 20:57.473
- Olivia's right.

20:57.517 --> 20:59.736
You'll understand
when you're older.

20:59.780 --> 21:02.173
- Then why did those men
wanna hurt me?

21:02.217 --> 21:03.392
- [sighs]

21:03.436 --> 21:05.481
I don't know.

21:05.525 --> 21:09.224
Some people are just--
they're just bad.

21:09.268 --> 21:12.662
- And what's important
is to surround yourself

21:12.706 --> 21:14.664
with people that are good.

21:14.708 --> 21:16.840
- Like you guys?
- Yeah.

21:16.884 --> 21:18.320
Like us.

21:18.364 --> 21:20.496
We're gonna take care of you.

21:20.540 --> 21:23.760
- We'll make sure
that no one hurts you.

21:23.804 --> 21:25.327
Again.

21:25.371 --> 21:27.111
- Thank you, Olivia.

21:27.155 --> 21:28.504
- Oh.

21:28.548 --> 21:31.681
♪

21:31.725 --> 21:34.205
[chuckles]

21:34.249 --> 21:37.034
Okay.
Let's get some rest.

21:37.078 --> 21:44.128
♪

21:45.826 --> 21:48.219
- That felt...
- Good.

21:48.263 --> 21:52.006
[NEEDTOBREATHE's
"Don't Bring That Trouble"]

21:52.049 --> 21:55.270
♪

21:55.314 --> 21:56.880
- Hey, here you go.

21:56.924 --> 21:58.621
- When do you think
I'll grow again?

21:58.665 --> 22:00.536
- Well, if you keep downing
burgers like that,

22:00.580 --> 22:02.538
you'll be as tall
as me by dinner.

22:02.582 --> 22:05.106
- [chuckles]

22:05.149 --> 22:07.543
- Hey.

22:07.587 --> 22:09.371
- Don't we know each other?

22:09.415 --> 22:10.546
- Nope.
[chuckles]

22:10.590 --> 22:12.331
I just have one of those faces.

22:12.374 --> 22:14.507
- One of those beautiful faces.

22:14.550 --> 22:16.639
- Oh.
Look.

22:16.683 --> 22:20.556
I live alone with my cat,
and I like it that way.

22:20.600 --> 22:22.428
- Well, that's one lucky pet.

22:22.471 --> 22:24.908
[both chuckle]

22:24.952 --> 22:26.910
Oh, come on.

22:26.954 --> 22:29.260
Can't blame a guy for trying.

22:29.304 --> 22:32.960
- Are you two into some kind
of weird role playing now?

22:33.003 --> 22:34.222
- Hardly.

22:34.265 --> 22:37.834
I found out there's a curse
on my family.

22:37.878 --> 22:43.100
Anyone I find
real love with dies.

22:43.144 --> 22:44.841
- Wait, what?

22:44.885 --> 22:46.408
- I had to make Bobo forget me.

22:46.452 --> 22:48.062
I put a tincture in his coffee.

22:48.105 --> 22:50.717
I figured if he
doesn't know me,

22:50.760 --> 22:55.461
he can't love me
and then if he doesn't love me,

22:55.504 --> 22:56.810
he won't die.

22:56.853 --> 22:59.639
- So you "Eternal Sunshined"
him?

22:59.682 --> 23:02.076
- I didn't have a choice.

23:02.119 --> 23:04.774
Let's just hope the spell's
strong enough.

23:04.818 --> 23:06.733
- Wait, did he forget about us,
too?

23:06.776 --> 23:09.953
- No.
Just me.

23:09.997 --> 23:12.260
- But what if he falls
in love with you again?

23:12.303 --> 23:13.609
What if it's fate?

23:13.653 --> 23:14.697
- Can--Can we talk
about something else?

23:14.741 --> 23:17.221
Like, uh, how is Mary doing?

23:17.265 --> 23:19.441
- Oh, she's great.

23:19.485 --> 23:22.139
I'm the one that's a mess.

23:22.183 --> 23:25.621
I keep telling her
I'll protect her.

23:25.665 --> 23:27.797
I don't know what
I'm protecting her from.

23:27.841 --> 23:29.364
- You think someone
else is after her?

23:29.408 --> 23:31.061
- No.

23:31.105 --> 23:33.455
I mean, I--I have that covered,
but I am worried about why

23:33.499 --> 23:35.326
someone would be after her.

23:35.370 --> 23:39.243
- I'm looking for my daughter,
Sheila Barrone.

23:39.287 --> 23:41.811
Have you seen my daughter?

23:41.855 --> 23:45.075
Oh, no.
Wh--What happened?

23:45.119 --> 23:46.425
[dramatic music]

23:46.468 --> 23:49.297
- I--I'm so sorry.

23:52.213 --> 23:54.345
Your daughter died.

23:54.389 --> 23:55.477
- No.
- In childbirth.

23:55.521 --> 24:00.003
- No, no, no, no.

24:00.047 --> 24:04.138
- I'm sorry.
- What about the baby?

24:04.181 --> 24:05.574
- Grandma?

24:05.618 --> 24:07.924
♪

24:07.968 --> 24:09.970
- [gasps]

24:13.713 --> 24:14.104
.

24:14.148 --> 24:16.977
- How is this even possible?

24:17.020 --> 24:19.283
- I know it's hard to believe.

24:19.327 --> 24:21.242
- [sigh]
It's just--

24:21.285 --> 24:24.245
It's a lot to take in.

24:24.288 --> 24:28.467
Last week my Sheila
was still pregnant.

24:28.510 --> 24:33.863
And now my granddaughter's
a teenager.

24:33.907 --> 24:38.041
Because she's a werewolf?
- Actually, a were-tiger.

24:38.085 --> 24:40.174
[dramatic music]

24:40.217 --> 24:44.221
- And why is someone after her?

24:44.265 --> 24:45.701
Who are these men?

24:45.745 --> 24:49.488
- Uh, we don't know.
Yet.

24:49.531 --> 24:51.838
But she's safe here
till we figure it out.

24:53.883 --> 24:56.364
- This is all so crazy.

24:56.407 --> 24:59.672
I just can't believe it.

24:59.715 --> 25:03.806
And yet you look so much
like my Sheila.

25:05.416 --> 25:07.810
You must be my granddaughter.

25:10.334 --> 25:14.687
- Can you tell me more
about my mom and dad?

25:14.730 --> 25:16.427
- Oh.
[laughs]

25:16.471 --> 25:20.649
- Fiji and I will get refills
and let you two catch up.

25:22.303 --> 25:23.696
- When was this taken?

25:23.739 --> 25:26.263
- Oh, when they
first got married.

25:26.307 --> 25:28.222
And they were on a road trip.

25:28.265 --> 25:30.311
They went to Canada
because your mother

25:30.354 --> 25:31.878
had always wanted to go.

25:31.921 --> 25:33.923
- I want you to do one
of those magical DNA tests.

25:33.967 --> 25:37.579
Lipstick from Grace's mug
and a hair from Mary's sweater.

25:37.623 --> 25:41.017
- Uh, I think you're letting
your personal feelings

25:41.061 --> 25:43.106
get in the way.

25:43.150 --> 25:45.935
Mary's got a family.
That's a good thing.

25:45.979 --> 25:47.633
- [sighs]

25:47.676 --> 25:50.331
One photo and a sob story
doesn't prove anything.

25:50.374 --> 25:51.854
People are after her.

25:51.898 --> 25:55.075
- And you think that that
little old lady's one of them?

25:55.118 --> 25:56.380
- [sighs]

25:56.424 --> 25:59.775
[rock music playing]

25:59.819 --> 26:01.560
Do the test.

26:02.865 --> 26:04.432
- All right.

26:08.001 --> 26:09.698
- Hello?

26:09.742 --> 26:13.267
Can somebody--Can
somebody help me?

26:13.310 --> 26:14.834
Can you help me with my car?

26:14.877 --> 26:17.097
- I'm sorry, ma'am,
but I can't leave my desk.

26:17.140 --> 26:19.316
- Well, somebody's gotta
give me a jump.

26:19.360 --> 26:22.493
My battery's deader
than road kill.

26:22.537 --> 26:24.321
- As much as I'd
love to jump you,

26:24.365 --> 26:26.323
it--it's against state
regulation for me

26:26.367 --> 26:28.630
to abandon my post.
- Oh!

26:28.674 --> 26:32.329
If I'm late for court again,
they're gonna take custody

26:32.373 --> 26:34.244
of my twins.
[sniffs]

26:34.288 --> 26:39.946
And Jayden and Brayden,
they need their mama.

26:39.989 --> 26:42.557
[sighs]

26:42.601 --> 26:44.907
- Where's your car?
- Over here.

26:44.951 --> 26:46.779
Oh, thank you so much.

26:46.822 --> 26:50.957
♪

26:51.000 --> 26:52.872
[door closes]

26:52.915 --> 26:59.966
♪

27:17.984 --> 27:21.640
[whooshing]

27:21.683 --> 27:23.337
- Damn, it's cold in there.

27:23.380 --> 27:25.078
[exhales sharply]

27:25.121 --> 27:27.558
[spooky music]

27:27.602 --> 27:31.562
What are you doing here?
- Nice to see you, too.

27:31.606 --> 27:33.216
Why were you after Sheila?

27:33.260 --> 27:36.263
And what did you want
with that little girl?

27:36.306 --> 27:38.439
- Why should I tell you?

27:38.482 --> 27:40.093
- Because--
[clears throat]

27:40.136 --> 27:41.877
I'm one of you.

27:41.921 --> 27:44.053
- Ah, Bernardo Clan, eh?

27:44.097 --> 27:46.055
- You got it.

27:46.099 --> 27:48.231
Play your cards right,

27:48.275 --> 27:50.190
I can help you cross over.

27:50.233 --> 27:52.061
- Piss off, bengalo.

27:52.105 --> 27:53.541
- [chuckles]

27:53.584 --> 27:57.284
You know how long a John Doe
can lie in that drawer?

27:57.327 --> 27:58.720
You think you're cold now?

27:58.764 --> 28:01.201
Wait till you've been on
that slab for six months.

28:01.244 --> 28:03.725
- Okay!

28:03.769 --> 28:05.466
I'll tell you.

28:05.509 --> 28:08.599
My client runs a traveling
fight ring.

28:08.643 --> 28:12.255
Super underground.
With supernaturals.

28:12.299 --> 28:15.171
- Is that why you
wanted the girl?

28:15.215 --> 28:16.738
- She came from good stock.

28:16.782 --> 28:19.262
Her old man's a prized fighter.

28:19.306 --> 28:20.742
Big were-tiger.

28:20.786 --> 28:23.266
And his owner wanted
the girl back.

28:23.310 --> 28:24.964
- Who's the owner?

28:25.007 --> 28:26.922
- Ah.
Hmm.

28:26.966 --> 28:29.272
[chuckles]

28:29.316 --> 28:31.840
Baddest bitch around.

28:31.884 --> 28:33.929
- [laughs]

28:33.973 --> 28:37.324
[rock music plays]

28:37.367 --> 28:39.413
- Hey.
What'd you find out?

28:39.456 --> 28:41.763
- Grace is definitely
Mary's grandmother.

28:41.807 --> 28:43.460
- [sighs]

28:43.504 --> 28:45.071
- Oh, you okay?

28:45.114 --> 28:47.290
- Just because someone's blood
doesn't mean they have

28:47.334 --> 28:49.466
your best interests in mind.

28:49.510 --> 28:51.468
Trust me, I know.

28:51.512 --> 28:54.341
[cell phone rings]

28:54.384 --> 28:55.559
[beeps]

28:55.603 --> 28:58.519
Yeah?
- Gypsies are after Mary.

28:58.562 --> 29:00.303
They run a supernatural
fight ring.

29:00.347 --> 29:01.783
Force them to fight
to the death.

29:01.827 --> 29:03.916
It's run by this evil
old woman named--

29:03.959 --> 29:05.134
- Grace?
- Yeah.

29:05.178 --> 29:06.832
How'd you know?

29:14.274 --> 29:14.448
.

29:14.491 --> 29:17.712
[distant cheering]

29:17.756 --> 29:18.844
- [laughs]

29:18.887 --> 29:21.020
You get used to the smell.

29:21.063 --> 29:23.457
Hideous, aren't they?
- [grunts]

29:23.500 --> 29:27.940
- The only way to control
them is their collars.

29:27.983 --> 29:33.684
Silver for were,
gold for banshees.

29:33.728 --> 29:34.903
- [screeching]

29:34.947 --> 29:37.427
- And iron for demons.
- [groans]

29:37.471 --> 29:39.038
- [screeching]

29:39.081 --> 29:40.561
- Why are you doing this?

29:40.604 --> 29:43.172
- 'Cause you can turn a pretty
penny when you get them

29:43.216 --> 29:45.348
to battle to the death.

29:45.392 --> 29:48.221
- Is that what you're
gonna do to me?

29:48.264 --> 29:50.049
But I'm your granddaughter.

29:50.092 --> 29:51.964
- Your mother was a traitor.

29:52.007 --> 29:54.140
She shacked up with one
of these animals

29:54.183 --> 29:56.098
and defiled our
gypsy bloodline.

29:56.142 --> 29:59.101
When I found out what she did,
I locked her up.

29:59.145 --> 30:01.060
Just like them.

30:01.103 --> 30:02.844
But she escaped.

30:02.888 --> 30:04.237
- [groans]

30:04.280 --> 30:07.762
- There will be no escape
for you, Mary.

30:07.806 --> 30:09.546
- [groans]
- Mary.

30:09.590 --> 30:12.201
Is that you?

30:12.245 --> 30:15.248
I'm Mike.
Your father.

30:15.291 --> 30:17.119
- Dad?

30:17.163 --> 30:18.338
[electric buzzing]
- [groans]

30:18.381 --> 30:19.513
- No!

30:19.556 --> 30:20.775
- [heavy breathing]

30:20.819 --> 30:22.298
- [grunting]

30:22.342 --> 30:24.387
- I'm so sorry.
- [grunts]

30:24.431 --> 30:25.606
- [laughs]

30:26.999 --> 30:29.566
- We're gonna need
a distraction.

30:29.610 --> 30:30.872
- [sighs]

30:30.916 --> 30:32.526
You feel like going
in the ring?

30:32.569 --> 30:35.355
- Nothing I like better than
a little rage in the cage.

30:35.398 --> 30:37.836
- That should give you
and Joe cover to sneak in,

30:37.879 --> 30:39.402
find Mary,
and get out.

30:39.446 --> 30:41.796
- Not quite sure what
I bring to the game.

30:41.840 --> 30:44.930
- Honey, there's nothing more
distracting than a pretty girl.

30:44.973 --> 30:47.933
[suspenseful music]

30:47.976 --> 30:49.630
- All right.

30:56.071 --> 30:57.464
- You work here.

30:57.507 --> 31:01.250
- Well, it's my--it's my shop.
[giggles]

31:01.294 --> 31:02.861
I have a feeling you
already knew that.

31:02.904 --> 31:04.427
- [laughs]

31:04.471 --> 31:05.559
You got me.

31:05.602 --> 31:07.953
Full disclosure,
I was asking around town

31:07.996 --> 31:09.258
about you.

31:09.302 --> 31:12.174
- Well, the shop's closed.

31:12.218 --> 31:15.177
- Well, uh, the door was open.

31:17.658 --> 31:19.529
- I'm sorry, Bobo,
but I don't have time.

31:19.573 --> 31:22.968
I'm working on a protection
potion for Mary.

31:23.011 --> 31:24.752
[sighs]

31:24.795 --> 31:29.017
- Well, I can help with that.
- No.

31:32.629 --> 31:33.935
[both moaning]

31:33.979 --> 31:36.982
♪

31:37.025 --> 31:38.809
You remember.

31:38.853 --> 31:41.725
- Fiji, we...

31:41.769 --> 31:46.469
We were--We are--in love.

31:48.994 --> 31:52.519
[crowds cheering]

31:52.562 --> 31:55.652
- Hey, you gotta know
somebody to get in.

31:55.696 --> 31:57.480
- Bernardo Clan.

31:57.524 --> 31:59.134
[gun cocks]

32:00.919 --> 32:02.790
- Wanna see my tattoo?

32:02.833 --> 32:04.792
Yeah?
Right here.

32:04.835 --> 32:06.185
[gasps]

32:06.228 --> 32:08.796
Better yet, why don't I show
you on the way out?

32:08.839 --> 32:09.971
[giggles]

32:10.015 --> 32:12.582
Trust me,
it'll be worth the wait.

32:12.626 --> 32:15.020
- I'll be right here.
- All right, baby.

32:15.063 --> 32:16.717
